Help
----
arrows  = forward, backward, rotate heading
<mouse> = change heading, change pitch
<wheel-mouse> = change zoom (0)
a = strafe left
s = strafe right
d = debug camera
f = locked-y first-person
m = capture mouse
-/+ = mouse sensitivity (0.15)
q = quit

src
---
App.cpp        -- Run the game
Background.cpp -- Skybox to contain the gameworld
Boss.cpp       -- The boss characters
Camera.cpp     -- Camera class first person view
Engine.cpp     -- Setup SDL and start Main and App
Explosion.cpp  -- Handle explosions
Explosion2.cpp -- snowflake style explosions
Frustum.cpp    -- Viewing volume used by Player.cpp
glu.cpp        -- routines lifted from libglu
HUD.cpp        -- Heads Up Display
Input.cpp      -- Simple input class used to pass state from Main to App
Main.cpp       -- Handle input and App
Matrix.cpp     -- C matrix routines
Object.cpp     -- Visual Game Objects
Particle.cpp   -- Particle System for Explosions
Quaternion.cpp -- Quaternion representation of rotations
Rocket.cpp     -- shooting rocket
Rocket2.cpp    -- shooting rocket with gravity
Scenery.cpp    -- Immoveable objects
SDL_LoadImage.cpp -- convert SDL textures to opengl
Terrain.cpp    -- Fast terrain map [good for games]
Vector.cpp     -- Vector class

Require gcc-c++, and SDL-devel

